---
import SpokeLayout from '../../layouts/SpokeLayout.astro';
import StatCard from '../../components/pitch/StatCard.astro';
import TAMFunnel from '../../components/pitch/TAMFunnel.astro';
import MarketGrowthChart from '../../components/pitch/MarketGrowthChart.astro';
import marketData from '../../data/pitch/market-data.json';
---

<SpokeLayout
  title="Market Opportunity — CUPLA Proposal"
  description="The relationship app market and the nutrition app market together represent over $6.6B in annual consumer spending. Nobody has built the product that lives at their intersection."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="pt-20 md:pt-28 pb-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <span class="text-xs text-text-secondary font-medium uppercase tracking-wider">Market Opportunity</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-3 mb-6">The Market Is Real.<br/>The Category Doesn't Exist Yet.</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        The $1.8 billion meal planning headline is borrowed from the broad market — a figure that includes solo dieters, hospital nutrition software, and family recipe apps. That is not this product's market. This product sits at the intersection of <strong class="text-text-primary">two distinct, growing, and measurable markets</strong> — and nobody has built the product that lives where they overlap.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TWO MARKETS. ONE INTERSECTION. -->
  <section class="spoke-section-alt">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title text-center mb-8">Two Markets. One Intersection. Zero Products.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="pitch-card-sage">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">💑</span>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-sage-dark">Relationship Apps for Couples</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">Tools couples use to reduce friction, increase connection, and share daily life.</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold text-sage-dark">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.relationshipApps.market2025}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">2025</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold text-sage-dark">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.relationshipApps.market2034}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">By 2034</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold text-sage-dark">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.relationshipApps.cagr}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">CAGR</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card-terracotta">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">🥗</span>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-terracotta-dark">Diet & Nutrition Apps</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-4">Tools individuals use to track food, manage goals, and eat better.</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-center">
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold text-terracotta-dark">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.nutritionApps.market2025}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">2025</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold text-terracotta-dark">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.nutritionApps.market2030}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">By 2030</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-lg font-bold text-terracotta-dark">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.nutritionApps.cagr}</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary">CAGR</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="text-lg text-text-primary font-semibold mb-3">
          Combined: <span class="text-sage">{marketData.intersectingMarkets.combined}</span> in active consumer spending on the exact two problems this product solves.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">
          Neither market owns the overlap. No product has been built for couples who share a kitchen but have different dietary goals. That intersection is the category.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 text-xs text-text-secondary text-center">
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Sources:</strong> Relationship apps market from Market Reports World. Diet & nutrition apps market from Mordor Intelligence.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MARKET SIZE BREAKDOWN -->
  <section class="spoke-section">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title text-center mb-8">Market Size Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <StatCard number={marketData.intersectingMarkets.relationshipApps.market2025} label="Relationship Apps" sublabel="2025 — $854M → $2.6B by 2034" />
        <StatCard number={marketData.intersectingMarkets.nutritionApps.market2025} label="Nutrition Apps" sublabel="2025 — $5.76B → $10.15B by 2030" />
        <StatCard number={marketData.marketSize.cagr} label="AI Segment CAGR" sublabel="28.10% — the real tailwind" />
        <StatCard number="35M" label="US Couples (25-45)" sublabel="The starting point — Census data" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI MARKET GROWTH -->
  <section class="spoke-section-alt">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title text-center mb-4">The AI Segment Is the Real Tailwind</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-text-secondary mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">The AI-driven meal planning segment is growing at 28.1% CAGR — more than double the broader market rate. This signals that consumers are actively demanding intelligent, adaptive, personalized food solutions. Collaborative Adaptive Nutrition sits directly in this growth trajectory.</p>
      <MarketGrowthChart />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TAM / SAM / SOM -->
  <section class="spoke-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title text-center mb-4">TAM / SAM / SOM — Built From the Ground Up</h2>
      <p class="text-center text-text-secondary mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">Not borrowed from a broad market report. Built from census data, category analysis, and bottom-up logic.</p>
      <TAMFunnel />
      <div class="space-y-4 mt-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="badge-signature">TAM</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-lg">{marketData.tam.value}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">{marketData.tam.description}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-2 bg-cream-dark p-2 rounded border border-border">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">TAM derivation:</strong> The combined addressable market of relationship apps ($854M) and diet/nutrition apps ($5.76B) represents over $6.6B in active consumer spending on the exact two problems this product solves — relationship friction and individual nutrition. Capturing even a fraction of either justifies the business.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="badge-signature">SAM</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-lg">{marketData.sam.value}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">{marketData.sam.description}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-2 bg-cream-dark p-2 rounded border border-border">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">SAM derivation:</strong> 35M US couples aged 25-45 (Census Bureau). Approximately 20-30% — 7-10M households — are actively health-conscious with at least one partner tracking nutrition goals. At $10/month per household: $840M-$1.2B SAM. This is grounded, defensible, and does not rely on claiming a broad market that includes hospital dietetics and solo users.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <span class="badge-signature">SOM</span>
            <span class="font-bold text-lg">{marketData.som.value}</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">{marketData.som.description}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-2 bg-cream-dark p-2 rounded border border-border">
            <strong class="text-text-primary">Path to $1M ARR:</strong> 10,000 paying households at $10/month = $1.2M ARR. This represents 0.1-0.3% of the SAM — an extremely conservative target achievable through organic growth alone, without a single dollar of paid acquisition.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY THE CATEGORY DOESN'T EXIST YET -->
  <section class="spoke-section-alt">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title mb-6">Why the Category Doesn't Exist Yet</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="pitch-card-sage">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-sage-dark">Nutrition apps were built by nutritionists who think in macros</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">They bolt on "sharing" as an afterthought. Fitia's Sync Plan uses a master/slave model that reportedly deletes the receiving user's existing meal plan — this is not real-time collaboration, it is data transfer. You cannot retrofit a solo app to feel like it was built for two people from the ground up.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card-terracotta">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 text-terracotta-dark">Relationship apps were built for emotional connection</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">They have never touched nutrition intelligence. The "what should we eat?" argument is the most repeated daily friction point in a shared household — and no relationship app has built the system to solve it. The emotional positioning is there, but the product depth is not.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Neither camp built from the couples-sharing-a-kitchen perspective up</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">That is not a problem to explain away. <strong class="text-text-primary">That is the opportunity.</strong> The gap is structural, not accidental. The category of "real-time collaborative adaptive household nutrition" does not exist yet as a measured segment. Three independent AI analyses (Claude, Gemini, GPT) all concluded independently that nobody fully owns it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TARGET SEGMENTS -->
  <section class="spoke-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title text-center mb-8">Target Segment Breakdown</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {marketData.targetSegments.map((seg) => (
          <div class="pitch-card">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary">{seg.segment}</h3>
              <span class="text-sage font-bold text-lg">{seg.size}</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">{seg.notes}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 pitch-card">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Geographic Strategy — Why North America First</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-3">North America represents 34%+ of the global market — the largest regional share. But the strategic reasons go beyond market size:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-text-secondary">
          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">English-first market:</strong> AI meal generation works best in English. Expanding to other languages requires model fine-tuning and cultural adaptation.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">PWA-friendly:</strong> iOS and Android adoption is high. PWA install rates are strong. No app store gatekeeping needed for initial launch.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Health-conscious culture:</strong> Post-pandemic health awareness, fitness tracking adoption, and meal prep culture are all strongest in North America.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-text-primary">Couples cooking together:</strong> Remote work has increased home cooking frequency. The "what's for dinner?" argument is universal but most acute in dual-income households.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-3">International expansion (Europe, Asia-Pacific) follows after product-market fit in North America. The architecture is designed for global deployment — localization is the only barrier.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MARKET GROWTH DRIVERS -->
  <section class="spoke-section-alt">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title text-center mb-8">Market Growth Drivers</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">Health consciousness rising (post-pandemic trend)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Home cooking increased 54% during the pandemic and has not fully reverted. Fitness tracking adoption continues to grow across all demographics.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">Remote work = more home cooking</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">Hybrid and remote work means more meals at home. Couples are cooking together more frequently, increasing the need for coordinated meal planning.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">AI capabilities improving rapidly</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">LLM quality for recipe generation, nutritional analysis, and natural language understanding has improved dramatically. The product gets better as models improve — no engineering required.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">Mental load conversation gaining cultural traction</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">The concept of "mental load" in relationships has entered mainstream discourse. Products that reduce it have a cultural tailwind and built-in marketing narrative.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">Couples pursuing fitness goals together</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">More couples are cooking at home, tracking nutrition, and pursuing fitness goals simultaneously. This creates the exact use case for adaptive shared cooking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">Food waste awareness driving pantry-first solutions</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">The average household wastes $1,500/year in food. Pantry-first approaches directly address this. The sustainability angle adds cultural relevance.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-white rounded-xl border border-border md:col-span-2">
          <span class="text-sage text-lg mt-0.5">↑</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-text-primary font-medium">PWA adoption eliminating app store barriers</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mt-1">iOS 16.4+ added full PWA support including push notifications and home screen installation. The technical barriers to PWA distribution are disappearing. This means zero app store review process, instant deployment, and global edge delivery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPETITIVE REVENUE ANCHORS -->
  <section class="spoke-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title mb-6">The Market Is Validated — By Competitors Charging Real Money</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6">This is not speculative. Existing products in adjacent categories are generating real revenue right now:</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="comparison-table w-full">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="rounded-tl-xl">Competitor</th>
              <th>Revenue / Traction</th>
              <th>Users</th>
              <th class="rounded-tr-xl">What This Proves</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">Fitia</td>
              <td>~$3.5M/year</td>
              <td>10M+</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">Nutrition apps can generate real revenue. Willingness to pay is proven.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">Eat This Much</td>
              <td>Bootstrapped, profitable</td>
              <td>6M+</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">AI meal planning is a sustainable business model.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">Yummo</td>
              <td>$9.99/mo per user</td>
              <td>Unknown</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">Adaptive portions concept has proven willingness to pay — EU only, zero marketing.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">DuoDine</td>
              <td>Free app, no revenue</td>
              <td>1,000+ couples</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">Demand exists before the full product exists. A free, basic couples meal app with no AI and no nutrition features still attracts 1,000+ active couples.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">Cloche</td>
              <td>Pre-launch</td>
              <td>500+ waitlist</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">A couples food app that hasn't launched yet has 500+ sign-ups. Demand exists before the product ships.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">Cozi</td>
              <td>Revenue-funded</td>
              <td>17M+</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">Family/household organization is a paying market.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="font-semibold">Listonic</td>
              <td>Bootstrapped</td>
              <td>20M+ downloads</td>
              <td class="text-text-secondary text-xs">Grocery list apps have massive user bases.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 pitch-card-sage">
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">
          <strong class="text-sage-dark">Key insight:</strong> The market is not waiting to be created. It is waiting to be served properly. Fitia alone generates $3.5M/year with a clinical, single-user nutrition app. A collaborative, relationship-first, adaptive cooking product serving the same market with a superior value proposition can reasonably target the same or higher revenue.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THREE INDEPENDENT VALIDATIONS -->
  <section class="spoke-section-alt">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title mb-6">Three Independent AI Validations</h2>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-6">This is not one analyst's opinion. Three independent AI systems (Claude, Gemini, GPT) were each given the same market analysis task and reached the same conclusion independently:</p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">All Three Concluded:</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">"Nobody fully owns the category of real-time collaborative adaptive household nutrition." The market is fragmented, not empty. The pieces exist separately but no single product occupies the center of the Venn diagram.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">All Three Identified:</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">The convergence trend — Fitia adding shared features, Yummo validating adaptive portions, Leanlife proving emotional positioning demand. The center is being approached from multiple directions but has not been claimed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pitch-card">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">All Three Recommended:</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary">Speed to market as the primary strategy. The window is open now but will narrow as competitors add pieces of the stack. First-mover advantage in category definition is the key strategic lever.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- KEY INSIGHT -->
  <section class="spoke-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="proposal-section-title mb-4">The Pitch in One Sentence</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        The relationship app market and the nutrition app market together represent over <strong class="text-sage">$6.6B in annual consumer spending</strong>. Nobody has built the product that lives at their intersection. The category is open. <strong class="text-text-primary">The timing is now.</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-4 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        The broader meal planning market is $1.8B — but this product is not chasing all of it. It is targeting the 35M US couples actively navigating different dietary goals. That is a <strong class="text-text-primary">$840M-$1.2B SAM</strong> that nobody has purpose-built for.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SOURCES & NOTES -->
  <section class="spoke-section-alt">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-text-secondary mb-4">Sources &amp; Notes</h2>
      <ol class="text-xs text-text-secondary space-y-2">
        <li><sup>1</sup> Relationship apps for couples market ($854M in 2025, growing to $2.6B by 2034 at 13.35% CAGR): Market Reports World, "Relationship Apps for Couples Market" (2025).</li>
        <li><sup>2</sup> Diet & nutrition apps market ($5.76B in 2025, forecast to reach $10.15B by 2030 at 12% CAGR): Mordor Intelligence, "Diet and Nutrition Apps Market" (2025).</li>
        <li><sup>3</sup> Overall meal planning app market ($1.8B → $5.2B at 12.5% CAGR): Grand View Research, "Meal Planning App Market Size, Share &amp; Trends Analysis Report" (2024-2034 forecast). Referenced for context only — not claimed as this product's TAM.</li>
        <li><sup>4</sup> AI-driven meal planning segment ($972.1M → $11.6B at 28.1% CAGR): Market.us, "AI-Driven Meal Planning Apps Market" (2024-2034 forecast).</li>
        <li><sup>5</sup> North America market share (34%+): Regional market distribution data from industry analysis reports.</li>
        <li><sup>6</sup> U.S. couples households (25-45 age range, ~35M): U.S. Census Bureau, "Families and Living Arrangements" data tables (2025). See census.gov/topics/families.</li>
        <li><sup>7</sup> Health-conscious couples estimate (7-10M, 20-30%): Derived from Census household data × estimated health/fitness engagement rates. Not a primary source figure.</li>
        <li><sup>8</sup> SAM ($840M-$1.2B): Calculated as 7-10M health-conscious couples × $10/mo × 12 months. Bottom-up, defensible derivation from census data.</li>
        <li><sup>9</sup> Multi-goal households (3-5M): Derived estimate based on couples with divergent dietary/fitness goals.</li>
        <li><sup>10</sup> SOM ($1M+ ARR): 10,000 paying households × $10/mo = $1.2M ARR. Represents 0.1-0.3% of SAM.</li>
        <li><sup>11</sup> Competitor revenue figures (Fitia ~$3.5M/yr, etc.): Based on public filings, YC data, and industry estimates. Some figures are approximations.</li>
        <li><sup>12</sup> DuoDine (1,000+ active couples) and Cloche (500+ waitlist): Pre-launch and free-tier user validation data from public sources.</li>
        <li><sup>13</sup> Revenue projections are illustrative and based on organic growth assumptions. Actual results will vary based on market conditions, execution, and competitive dynamics.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BACK LINK -->
  <section class="spoke-section">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <a href="/proposal/" class="text-sage hover:text-sage-dark transition-colors font-medium">← Back to Proposal Hub</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</SpokeLayout>
